Sandra Ha of Zico Import Pty Ltd, a small family-owned company, said the demand for silicone skins and covers to cover the unpleasant images on the cartons had skyrocketed almost from scratch two months ago, when British American Tobacco, Britain's Imperial Tobacco, Philip Morris and Japan Tobacco lost a challenge to the law in Australia's Supreme Court.
