Fabrizio was 21 years old when he was confirmed positive for AIDS.
"It was like a bomb dropped on me," he recalled the moment of the announcement, which the doctor was trying to make "smoother", with no obvious success.
The boy hid it from his family.
He decided to take care of his illness alone and began to inquire about it; with such endeavor that he already celebrated his 43rd birthday.
He is undoubtedly one of the oldest patients in the HIV Unit of the Civil Hospital of Guadalajara (HCG), to which he arrived in 1994 after several battles.
