“Basketball has been my life.”
Reyes does not exaggerate in making that assertion.
The walls of his house, almost all decorated with photos and memorabilia that denote his wide trajectory, testify.
Bayamón in the heart
Of all, the ones he treasures with the most excitement are those that reminisce about his time with the Cowboys from the mid-50s as a player until 1982, when he served 15 years serving as co-powered or in charge of the franchise.
